{
  "text": "In this section, we provide the results obtained on each of the CLL datasets with manual analysis carried out by [CITATION_1] and when analyzed with the method in [CITATION_2] (Phylosub). The results are shown in Tables 17 -22. In the genotype matrices, each column denotes a subclone, as opposed to the haplotype in our analyses, and a 0 and a 1 denote the presence and absence of a mutation in a subclone, respectively. Also, the clonal proportion matrices show the proportions of each subclone in each of the samples. ",
